# Database & Migrations

## Models
- Inherit from `Base` in `app/models/base.py`
- Use explicit `__tablename__`, typed `Mapped[]` columns
- Add indexes for foreign keys and frequently filtered columns

## Migrations
- One Alembic revision per schema change: `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add plants table"`
- Review autogenerated migrations — fix nullable/reversible issues before committing
- Never edit applied migrations; add a new revision to fix mistakes
- Seed data belongs in migrations or a dedicated seed script, not in model `__init__`

## Risk flags
- Dropping columns without data migration
- Non-nullable column added to table with existing rows
- Missing `downgrade()` for reversible deploys
